I'll create a comprehensive step-by-step guide you can follow to set up the PowerCA Flutter app from scratch!

## ðŸš€ PowerCA Mobile - Complete Setup Guide

### Step 1: Create Flutter Project

```bash
# Create new Flutter project
flutter create powerca_mobile
cd powerca_mobile

# Open in your IDE
code . # for VS Code
# or
idea . # for Android Studio
```

### Step 2: Create Folder Structure

```bash
# Create all necessary folders
mkdir -p lib/core/{constants,config,errors,network,utils}
mkdir -p lib/features/auth/{data/{models,repositories,datasources},domain/{entities,repositories,usecases},presentation/{bloc,pages,widgets}}
mkdir -p lib/features/dashboard/presentation/{pages,widgets}
mkdir -p lib/features/jobs/{data/{models,repositories,datasources},domain/{entities,repositories,usecases},presentation/{bloc,pages,widgets}}
mkdir -p lib/features/work_diary/{data/{models,repositories,datasources},domain/{entities,repositories,usecases},presentation/{bloc,pages,widgets}}
mkdir -p lib/features/clients/{data/{models,repositories,datasources},domain/{entities,repositories,usecases},presentation/{bloc,pages,widgets}}
mkdir -p lib/features/reminders/{data/{models,repositories,datasources},domain/{entities,repositories,usecases},presentation/{bloc,pages,widgets}}
mkdir -p lib/features/staff/{data/{models,repositories,datasources},domain/{entities,repositories,usecases},presentation/{bloc,pages,widgets}}
mkdir -p lib/features/leave/{data/{models,repositories,datasources},domain/{entities,repositories,usecases},presentation/{bloc,pages,widgets}}
mkdir -p lib/shared/{widgets,extensions}
mkdir -p assets/{images,icons,fonts}
mkdir -p test/{unit,widget,integration}
```

