## ðŸ“‹ Next Steps - Feature Implementation Pattern

For each new feature (Jobs, Work Diary, Clients, etc.), follow this pattern:

### 1. Domain Layer (Business Logic)
```
domain/
  â”œâ”€â”€ entities/         # Pure business objects
  â”œâ”€â”€ repositories/     # Abstract interfaces
  â””â”€â”€ usecases/        # Business logic operations
```

### 2. Data Layer (Data Management)
```
data/
  â”œâ”€â”€ models/          # JSON models (extend entities)
  â”œâ”€â”€ repositories/    # Concrete implementations
  â””â”€â”€ datasources/     # API calls, local storage
```

### 3. Presentation Layer (UI)
```
presentation/
  â”œâ”€â”€ bloc/           # State management (events, states, bloc)
  â”œâ”€â”€ pages/          # Screen widgets
  â””â”€â”€ widgets/        # Reusable components
```

### Example: Jobs Feature Structure

```dart
// 1. Entity (domain/entities/job.dart)
class Job {
  final int id;
  final String title;
  final String status;
  // ... properties
}

// 2. Repository Interface (domain/repositories/job_repository.dart)
abstract class JobRepository {
  Future<Either<Failure, List<Job>>> getJobs();
}

// 3. Use Case (domain/usecases/get_jobs_usecase.dart)
class GetJobsUseCase {
  final JobRepository repository;
  Future<Either<Failure, List<Job>>> call() => repository.getJobs();
}

// 4. BLoC Events (presentation/bloc/job_event.dart)
abstract class JobEvent {}
class LoadJobs extends JobEvent {}

// 5. BLoC States (presentation/bloc/job_state.dart)
abstract class JobState {}
class JobsLoaded extends JobState {
  final List<Job> jobs;
}

// 6. BLoC (presentation/bloc/job_bloc.dart)
class JobBloc extends Bloc<JobEvent, JobState> {
  final GetJobsUseCase getJobsUseCase;
  // Handle events...
}

// 7. Page (presentation/pages/jobs_page.dart)
class JobsPage extends StatelessWidget {
  // Use BlocBuilder to display data
}
```

